<section class="how-it-works">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>How DesignGenie Works</h2>

        <ol class="steps">
            <li>
                <h3>1. Enter Your Constraints</h3>
                <p>Start by specifying the shape, size, and material for your design. These inputs guide the AI in generating relevant options.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>2. Let AI Generate Variants</h3>
                <p>DesignGenie processes your constraints and generates multiple intelligent design options using AI models.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>3. Preview and Compare</h3>
                <p>You can view all generated designs visually and compare their structures, efficiency, and aesthetics.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>4. Refine Your Design</h3>
                <p>Modify any constraint and regenerate to see instant updates. Iterate as many times as needed for perfection.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>5. Optimize with AI</h3>
                <p>The system fine-tunes your selected design using advanced optimization, including topology techniques for better performance.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>6. Export & Save</h3>
                <p>Once satisfied, download your final design in PNG format and use it in your workflows or presentations.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

